Here is an example of a Discord.js v14 bot that has one command, "ban", which is a slash command. This bot will ban a user from the server if they are specified in the message.

First, you will need to install the `discord.js` library and create a new Discord bot instance:
```
const discord = require('discord.js');
const client = new discord.Client();
```
Next, you will need to create a new event handlers for the "ban" command:
```
client.on('message', async message => {
  if (message.content === 'ban') {
    const user = message.mentions.users.first();
    if (user) {
      const reason = message.content.split(' ').slice(1).join(' ');
      const channel = message.channel.id;
      const server = message.server.id;

      await message.guild.ban(user, reason, { reason, channel, server });
      message.author.send(`User ${user.username} has been banned from ${channel} by ${message.author.username}.`);
    } else {
      message.reply('Please specify a user to ban.');
    }
  }
});
```
This code will listen for the "ban" command and will ban a user if they are specified in the message. The bot will then send a message to the user who was banned, and will also send a message to the server's owner informing them of the ban.

Please note that this code is just an example and may need to be modified to fit your specific use case. Additionally, this code will only work if the server and channel are mentioned in the message.

